    <item>
      <title>Simple Player Balancing</title>
      <author>Catchy</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/548543</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/548543#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">ba023eb8e11c256c082dbdcc94933bc10add7f5b</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 Oct 2024 07:35:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670cc99131faf.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670cc9a1ee6b9.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;Hey, this was a mod that I made for myself personally, but I figured I would share it with all of you because, well, why not, I guess? It makes a number of changes, as well as a number of nerfs.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Gloom Damage is accrued very quickly, meaning to avoid gloom as almost any cost, as if you take damage, you will have to eat something that gets rid of it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Skydiving by default is a little bit faster&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Climbing is quite a bit faster&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Swimming is considerably faster&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Damage received is doubled&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Spring Water heals much faster&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Light Footprints appear more often and last a bit longer&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Zonai batteries regenerate a bit faster&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod doesn't change a whole lot, but I hope it can add a healthy balance of difficulty and also less tedium to your game at the same time.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Pairs very nicely with &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/514343"&gt;Vanilla+&lt;/a&gt;!</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/simple_player_balancing_9c0c8.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Player</category>
      <category>Effects</category>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>High Quality Weapon Icon Tool</title>
      <author>heydo6</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/548511</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/548511#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">06017195b7c28fd99c0f20dcec6901a4b57a255b</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 Oct 2024 06:02:25 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670cac8e8cf1a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c8d27eb2d3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c8c434d15a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c8c5b253c7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c9f947298f.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c9fc8c2f17.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c8c72a6925.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c8c7e1e5f0.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;High Quality Weapon Icon Tool&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Things you'll need...&lt;br&gt;-&amp;nbsp; This mod &lt;br&gt;- &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/480138"&gt;UltraCam&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt;- Image editing software&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Very simple mod which changes the textures of "FldObj_WoodStorage" &lt;br&gt;Works with &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;all versions&lt;/span&gt; and requires &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;no RSTB edits&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br&gt;Simply drop the mod in an emulator and toggle on/off when needed. &lt;br&gt;If you're familiar with image editing software you can take a picture and &lt;br&gt;and create a high quality icon in a few minutes. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Getting Started&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Install mod and UltraCam on emulator &lt;br&gt;- Drop the desired weapon on the wood storage platform&lt;br&gt;- Toggle on UltraCam, line up camera on weapon&lt;br&gt;- Adjust time of day, lighting with UltraCam&amp;nbsp; ( - &amp;amp; + ) on controller&lt;br&gt;- Take a few pictures of weapon or item&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Note:&lt;/span&gt; Weapons don't always line up at 45 degree, take the time to get the angle correct. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Image software&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Open your image in Photoshop &lt;br&gt;- Crop image of weapon similar to vanilla Icons &lt;br&gt;- Resize your cropped image to 288x288 &lt;br&gt;- Open Magic Wand tool and outline the edge of your weapon precisely&lt;br&gt;- Copy the image &lt;br&gt;- Open Eraser Tool and erase entire image&lt;br&gt;- Paste image and move to desired position &lt;br&gt;or&lt;br&gt;- Have a blank image 288x288 and paste there&lt;br&gt;- &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Save as png&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The white textured background makes creating a precise outline with Magic Wand tool quick and easy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Default texture is white, I've also included a black texture for white weapons, items.&lt;br&gt;If you don't understand any of these terms try a quick Google search.&lt;br&gt;Example... "How to use Magic Wand with Photoshop"&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is out of the scope of this mod but quick run down of the steps in Switch Toolbox.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Replacing image with Switch Toolbox&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;- Copy a donor Icon from your game dump&lt;br&gt;- Rename donor Icon, if needed &lt;br&gt;- Drop file into Switch ToolBox &lt;br&gt;- Rename all internal names, if needed &lt;br&gt;- Right click and replace image with the png we created&lt;br&gt;- Save&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sorry, didn't want this to turn into a guide just quickly run through the steps.&lt;br&gt;I've been using this method a while without much downside. &lt;br&gt;Quick and quality Icons even with complicated models.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Hope you enjoy &amp;lt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/weapon_icon_creator.7z" type="application/x-7z-compressed"/>
      <category>Misc</category>
      <category>Models</category>
    </item>
